/*The variable demoElement is assigned the element with the id "demo" using document.getElementById("demo").
  The value of inputValue is then assigned to the innerHTML property of demoElement.
  the below code is only for one single input to be dispalyed on the page
  var demoElement=document.getElementById("demo");
  demoElement.innerHTML=inputValue;*/

  /* In the line listItem.classList.add("list-item"), classList is a property of an element that represents a collection of the element's CSS classes. The add() method of the classList property is used to add a CSS class to the element.*/
  /* var listItem = document.createElement("p");: This line creates a new <p> element using document.createElement.
   This new element will be used to display the entered value.
  listItem.innerText = inputValue;: This line assigns the value of inputValue to the innerText property of the listItem element.
   It sets the text content of the <p> element to the entered value.
  
  var listContainer = document.getElementById("listContainer");: This line retrieves the element with the id "listContainer" from the HTML page. 
  It will serve as the container for the list items.
  listContainer.appendChild(listItem);: This line appends the listItem element (the new <p> element with the entered value) as a child to the listContainer element.
  This adds the new item to the list, displaying it on the webpage within the container.*/